+{"id":"bd-4kq0.5","title":"Text Wrap: Knuth-Plass DP (Optimal Raggedness)","description":"## Goal
Upgrade existing greedy wrap to an optional Knuth‑Plass dynamic programming line‑breaking algorithm for optimal raggedness and stability.

## Core Idea
Minimize total badness: sum (slack^3 + penalty) across lines, while respecting Unicode grapheme boundaries. Use DP with breakpoints; complexity O(n^2) with pruning.

## Acceptance Criteria
- Produces more stable and visually balanced line breaks.\n- Deterministic output given input and width.\n- Fallback to greedy mode for performance‑critical paths.

## Subtasks
- Knuth‑Plass math spec + penalties\n- Implementation with pruning\n- Tests + perf regression gates","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-02T23:20:18.672972510Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-02T23:20:18.672972510Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-4kq0.5","depends_on_id":"bd-4kq0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-02T23:20:18.672972510Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
+{"id":"bd-4kq0.5.1","title":"Knuth-Plass Spec (Badness + Penalties)","description":"## Goal
Define the exact badness function and DP formulation for line breaking.

## Math Spec
For line i with slack s_i = width − line_width:
- badness_i = (s_i / width)^3 * 1000
- Add penalties for hyphenation or forced breaks.
Objective: minimize total badness.
Use DP: cost[j] = min_i (cost[i] + badness(i→j) + penalty(i→j)).

## Tests (REQUIRED)
- unit_badness_monotone: larger slack => higher badness.\n- unit_penalty_applied: explicit penalties affect breaks.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-02T23:20:24.086500710Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-02T23:20:24.086500710Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-4kq0.5.1","depends_on_id":"bd-4kq0.5","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-02T23:20:24.086500710Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
+{"id":"bd-4kq0.5.2","title":"Knuth-Plass Implementation + Pruning","description":"## Goal
Implement DP line breaking with pruning to keep performance acceptable.

## Implementation Notes
